ies on different public policies. British scholars, practitioners and students are introduced all too rarely to ideas from the Francophone world, and this book will contribute to remedying that. It will be particularly relevant for students and practitioners of public administration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPolicy sciences. 0aPolitical planningxEvaluation. 0aPublic administration. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aLarrue, Corinne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVarone, Frederic, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978184742904940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847422309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847422309/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles